=== Verb ===
'''to martyr''' (''past'' and ''past participle:'' [[martyred]])

#To put to death for adhering to some belief, especially Christianity; to sacrifice on account of faith or profession.
#To persecute; to torment; to torture.
#:''The lovely Amoret, whose gentle heart'' 
#:''Thou martyrest with sorrow and with smart.'' —Spenser
